      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C conventional (160°C fan). Grease a 12-hole muffin tin. Combine the ground almonds, pistachios, sugar, and cinnamon. Roll into 12 equal balls. Separate the kataifi into 12 loose portions. Drizzle each portion with melted butter and toss gently to coat the strands. Press a nut ball into the centre of each portion and wrap the strands around it, forming a nest shape. Press into the greased muffin holes. Brush the top generously with remaining melted butter.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 22 to 26 minutes until evenly golden. Meanwhile, make the syrup: combine the sugar, water, and honey in a small saucepan, bring to the boil, then simmer for 3 minutes. Remove from the heat and stir in the rosewater and lemon juice. As soon as the nests come from the oven, spoon the hot syrup over them generously, letting it soak in. Leave to cool in the tin for 20 minutes before transferring. Scatter with extra chopped pistachios.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
